<h2>imagesLoaded</h2>

<p>Unloaded images can throw off Isotope layouts and cause item elements to overlap. <a href="https://imagesloaded.desandro.com">imagesLoaded</a> resolves this issue.</p>

<p>Initialize Isotope, then trigger <a href="methods.html#layout"><code>layout</code></a> after each image loads.</p>

<div class="duo example">
  <div class="duo__cell example__code">
    ``` js
    // init Isotope
    var $grid = $('.grid').isotope({
      // options...
    });
    // layout Isotope after each image loads
    $grid.imagesLoaded().progress( function() {
      $grid.isotope('layout');
    });
    ```
  </div>
  <div class="duo__cell example__demo">
    {{> imagesloaded-progress}}
  </div>
</div>

<p>Or, initialize Isotope after all images have been loaded.</p>

<div class="duo example">
  <div class="duo__cell example__code">
    ``` js
    var $grid = $('.grid').imagesLoaded( function() {
      // init Isotope after all images have loaded
      $grid.isotope({
        // options...
      });
    });
    ```
  </div>
  <div class="duo__cell example__demo">
    {{> imagesloaded-callback}}
  </div>
</div>

